cess but also a sexual one. She demonstrates how the "specter of the fag" becomes a disciplinary mechanism for regulating heterosexual as well as homosexual boys and how the "fag discourse" is as much tied to gender as it is to sexuality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGender identity. 0aHeterosexuality. 0aHigh school studentszCaliforniaxSocial conditions. 0aIdentity (Psychology) in adolescence. 0aMasculinity. 0aSocialization. 0aTeenage boyszCaliforniaxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095069640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950696/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles